{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nImplementing this epic's session-provenance fold (`_fold_claimed_session`, stories 68ef +\nc557) added the claiming-session/harness fold to `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py`, which was\nalready at EXACTLY the 800-LOC module-size soft cap on `main`. The additions pushed it to 832,\ntripping the CI module-size gate. Rather than allowlist it (grow the grandfathered over-cap\nset), split the file along the clean seam that already exists: the per-event **processors**\nvs the two-pass **replay engine**.\n\n## What\n- **New module `src/rebar/reducer/_replay.py`** ‚Äî move the replay ENGINE out of\n  `_processors.py`: `scan_for_latest_snapshot`, `_ReplayCtx`, the flat `_EVENT_HANDLERS`\n  dispatch table, and `replay_events`. This is a one-way dependency (the engine imports the\n  `process_*` processors; the processors never call the engine), so it is a clean seam.\n- **`_processors.py`** keeps ONLY the per-event `process_*` fold functions; drop the\n  now-unused imports (`Callable`, `NamedTuple`, `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`, `TAG_DELTA` ‚Äî all were\n  used solely by the engine/handler-table). Result: `_processors.py` drops from 832 to ~652\n  LOC, back under the 800 soft cap with no allowlist change.\n- **Importers** ‚Äî `reducer/_api.py` and `reducer/__init__.py` import `replay_events` /\n  `scan_for_latest_snapshot` from `._replay` instead of `._processors` (and the `__init__`\n  module docstring's provenance note is updated).\n- **Test** ‚Äî `tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_tag_delta.py::test_downgraded_clone_preserves_and_ignores`\n  monkeypatches `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES` / `TAG_DELTA`; retarget those patches from `_processors`\n  to `_replay` (the module the replay loop now reads them from).\n- Pure move ‚Äî NO behavior change; the reducer's public API (`reduce_ticket`, `replay_events`,\n  `scan_for_latest_snapshot`, the `process_*` functions) is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the file move (`_replay.py`), the `_processors.py` trim + import cleanup, the two\n  importer updates, and the one test monkeypatch retarget.\n- OUT: any behavior change; further reducer decomposition; the session-provenance feature\n  itself (stories 68ef / c557 / 199b).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` is under the 800-LOC soft cap (no allowlist/ceilings\n      entry added). Proof: `test -$(wc -l < src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py) -lt -800` ‚Äî i.e.\n      `wc -l < src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` prints < 800.\n- [ ] `src/rebar/reducer/_replay.py` exists and holds `replay_events`,\n      `scan_for_latest_snapshot`, `_ReplayCtx`, and `_EVENT_HANDLERS`. Proof:\n      `grep -c \"def replay_events\\|def scan_for_latest_snapshot\\|_EVENT_HANDLERS\" src/rebar/reducer/_replay.py`.\n- [ ] The public reducer API still imports and works: `replay_events` /\n      `scan_for_latest_snapshot` resolve from `rebar.reducer`, and `reduce_ticket` is unchanged.\n      Proof: `python -c \"from rebar.reducer import replay_events, scan_for_latest_snapshot, reduce_ticket\"`.\n- [ ] The module-size CONTRACT test passes (no over-cap drift). Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`.\n- [ ] The reducer test suite (incl. the retargeted downgraded-clone test) stays green. Proof:\n      `pytest tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_tag_delta.py -q` and the full\n      `tests/scripts/reducer/` directory.\n\n## Depends on\n- (none ‚Äî a mechanical extraction; lands as the BASE of the session-provenance stack so the\n  fold-bearing commits stay under the cap.)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783556234593651001,"uuid":"191089c8-5f74-4a4a-b13f-309dcf548b1e"}